<div class="quotetitle">mkwong98 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br /><div class="quotetitle">8bitMicroGuy wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Awesome! So original and new! I've never seen an emulator like this. It's great! Now, when the cartridge bankswitches, how do you manage to keep track of which sprite goes where?<br />I think you should do the following<br />Name every HD sprite as the hex sequence of the sprite's data and 3 colors from the palette. For example: 01020408102040800103070F1F3F7FFF2C2E31<br />That way every sprite, wherever it comes from, will have its HD sprite.<br /></div><br /><br />In HDNes, the mappers return the real address of the read so bankswitching is not a problem.</div><br /><br />What about Battletoads where the player sprites are loaded by copypasting from PRG-ROM to CHR-RAM?<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=6924">8bitMicroGuy</a> — Thu Apr 02, 2015 2:49 pm</p><hr />
